---> A Linux shell script is a text file containing a series of commands that are executed in sequence by a shell interpreter. It is used for automating tasks, performing system operations, and creating simple to complex programs on Unix-like operating systems. Shell scripts are written in a shell language (such as Bash) and enable users to automate tasks and execute multiple commands in a specific order from the command line.

